CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 28, 1950, pg. A13 reads: "Chest Volunteer Solicitors - These volunteer solicitors fro the Community Chest will be doing their community and ninety-six agencies which serve it a great service in near future when they knock on doors between Centre Avenue and Fifth Avenue, and Dinwiddie and Fullerton Streets, gathering funds and pledges for the Community Chest. Left to right, seated: Florence Williams, Mrs. Mary Lee Mills, Richard Flaherty, Genevieve Sanders and Celesta Davis. Standing: Calvin Hill and Willis Collins. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Community Chest volunteer solicitors, from left, seated: Florence Williams, Mary Lee Mills, Richard Flaherty, Genevieve Sanders, and Celesta Davis; standing: Calvin Hill and Willis Collins, gathered around table in interior with two large windows, wood paneling, and clock on wall that reads "12:40"
